================================================================================================================================
Nmap is a industry standard tool for network discovery and security auditing
-> Open source tool that sends specially crafted packets to a target IP address and analyze response to create a "map" of network
-> USES :- network inventory  :- find out what devices are actually connected to wifi
           security auditing  :-finding open doors hackers might use
           Troubleshooting    :- check if firtewall is accidentally blocking your web server
Note :- read TCP/IP concepts or ask chatgpt
SYNTAX
      nmap [scan logic] [options] [target]
Big 4 :- 
       -sS  SYN scan - sends SYN receives SYN/ACK and sends RST doesnt complete connection
       -sT  connect scan - completes 3 way handshake
       -sV  version scan - interogates open ports to find sockets 
       -0   OS detection - guesses the OS 
basic code 
  nmap -v -A scanme.nmap.org  ---> basic example u can try
======================PORT STATUS===============================
 open : running and accepting connections
 closed : accesible , no app is listening on it
 filtered : firewall is blocking access
 ====================================================================================================================================
